address: 160 Convensia-daero, Songdo-dong, Yeonsu-gu, Incheon, South Korea
description: Located in Songdo International New City, Central Park is a green rest space covering an area of about 400,000 square meters. The artificial lake in the park is shaped like the Korean peninsula, and 12-seater and 32-seater (weekend) water taxis are available for tourists along the 1.2-kilometer long sea route. Tourists who need to ride can book in advance, or they can take the bus on a first-come-first-served basis on the day.

address: 48 Sogong-ro, Hoehyeon-dong, Jung-gu, Seoul, South Korea
description: Seoul Animation Center, located in Seoul, South Korea, is a fun parent-child paradise. Children can not only take pictures with the cartoon characters here, but also read books in the comic library.

The Olympic Swimming Stadium is located in the Seoul Olympic Park, near North Gate 2. This is a swimming pool with world-class water quality and international scale, which can accommodate more than 10,000 spectators at the same time, and has complete swimming, diving, training and other swimming pool facilities. The Olympic Swimming Stadium is located outside the east gate of Tucheng in Mengcun, and the transportation is very convenient. The whole building is divided into 4 floors underground and 3 floors above ground. There are also DOPPIO cafes, CU convenience stores, and children's playgrounds in the venue. Next to the Olympic Swimming Stadium is the Olympic Gymnastics Gymnasium.
